The paper deals with semantic object segmentation using deep convolutional neural networks (DCNNs), which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also focuses on weakly supervised learning, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of saliency maps and image-level annotations suggests a potential connection to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
